cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.Medical Imaging, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the task of detecting and localizing fetal anatomical regions in 2D ultrasound images using convolutional neural network architectures. This task falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of soft proposal layers and weakly supervised learning also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the application of this work in medical imaging and healthcare makes it relevant to the medical imaging (cs.Medical Imaging) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks for detection and localization tasks suggests the involvement of neural engineering (cs.NE) techniques.
